The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation

 Teamwork on terror

 New Delhi, Jan. 25: India and Saudi Arabia today decided to work together in tackling terrorism and sealed an accord to combat crime, but did not sign an extradition treaty.

 Prime Minister Manmohan Singh and King Abdullah, the first Saudi monarch to visit the country, also discussed economic cooperation.

 A foreign ministry spokesman said the king underlined the need to work together on terror and said his nation had called a war on the scourge.




